update comment set body='     <I>         A clear research question couples your selected data with analysis tools. There are four basic tools; which one you use depends on the information you are seeking.  You will execute these analysis routines on the Grid.  <P> The analysis tool bag contains:    <UL>    <LI><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'dpstutorial.jsp\',820)">Performance Study</a> - detector performance check.  <LI><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'ltimetutorial.jsp\',820)">Lifetime Study</a> - the particles in our detector.  <LI><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'fluxtutorial.jsp\',820)">Flux Study</A> - rate that cosmic rays hit a given area over time. <LI><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'eshtutorial.jsp\',820)">Shower Study</A> - multiple detectors lighting up at the same time. </UL>  </I>   <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=analysis_tools\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>  <P> <B>References</B>   <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'flash/analysis.html\',600,600)">Grid Virtual Data</a> - see the processing flow of your data through the Grid.<br/>  <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://www.th.physik.uni-frankfurt.de/~drescher/CASSIM/c10.mpg\',800,700)">Cosmic Ray Simulation</a> - animation of what a possible shower would look like (need QuickTime plugin)<br/> ' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='analysis_tools';
update comment set body='          <I>You need data to find answers to your research questions. Some groups in the collaboration have detectors. They arrange and setup their hardware to collect data. They upload data files to a central Grid fileserver so that they are available to everyone.  </I>    <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=collect_upload_data\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>  <P> <B>References</B>    <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'flash/daq_only_standalone.html\',600,600)">Detector Hardware</a> - the setup of the cosmic ray data collection components<br/>    <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'flash/DAQII.html\',800,800)">DAQ: data acquisition board</a> - working details of filtering data<br/>      <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'flash/daq_portal_rays.html\')">Grid: collection of machines</a> - how your data moves around the Grid<br/>       <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://gridcafe.web.cern.ch/gridcafe/\',800,650)">Grid Cafe</a> - learn more about the Grid.<br/>      <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="http://quarknet.fnal.gov/toolkits/ati/det-user.pdf">QuarkNet/Walta/CROP Cosmic Ray Detectors User\'s Manual</a> - instructions for the beginner and advanced user (pdf file)<br/>          <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'view-data.jsp\',650,600)">View Data</a> - want to see a sample of uploaded data? <br/>  ' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='collect_upload_data';
update comment set body='    <I>    Communication is a two-way street. You present results; your audience asks tough questions. This exchange can confirm your results, or it may identify gaps in your analysis and suggest ways to improve your research. Wide acceptance of your ideas means that you have satisfied your critics. <P> You ask questions of other student research teams, leave comments on posters, and respond to those left on your posters. This respectful back and forth discussion is DOING SCIENCE. </I>      <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=comment_poster\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>   <P> <B>References</B> <p>     <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'comments_poster_static.html\',950,600)">Example Comment Page</a> - comments gathered from many teams<br/>      <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://www.space.com/scienceastronomy/gravity_speed_030116.html\',800,600)">Science At Odds</a> - example of when science requires public discourse among experts to advance<br/>' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='comment_poster';
update comment set body='<I>All research centers on a single, well designed research question which scientists develop  by bridging from things they know into new territory.  They ask questions balanced between  simple and complex. <UL>   <LI>Too simple: it\'s already known and not interesting. <LI>Too complex: the question is intractable and unmanageable. </UL> <P>Research questions are also quided by the what is possible to measure. </I>    <P>Let\'s find a good research question.  Let\'s understand the experimental parameters.  <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'ref-cr-study.jsp\',500,610)">Cosmic Ray Studies</A> - refine your search about cosmic rays <P>   <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'studies.jsp\',850,600)">Studies with Classroom Detector</A> - what can the cosmic ray collaboration tools measure?    <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=cosmic_ray_study\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>  <P> <B>References</B>     <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://www.pas.rochester.edu/~pavone/particle-www/ParticleExperiments/index.htm\',1000,600)">PARTICLE at the University of Rochester</a> - experiments<br/>   <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://helios.gsfc.nasa.gov/qa_cr.html\',850,600)">COSMICOPIA</a> - Ask Us<br/> ' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='cosmic_ray_study';
update comment set body=' <I>All research starts with things you know. The path winds through areas of knowledge that you don\'t know, but will need to master. The starting point is the simple and well understood.<P></i>  <P>Let\'s describe cosmic rays in simple terms.<BR>  <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=cosmic_rays\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>     <P><B>References</B>    <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="http://hires.phys.columbia.edu/papers/CosmicExtremes.pdf">Cosmic Extremes</A> - Excellent cosmic ray overview available to print (pdf file)<br/>      <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://www2.slac.stanford.edu/vvc/cosmicrays/cratmos.html\',750,600)">SLAC: high energy cosmic rays</a> - read about cosmic rays<br/>      <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://imagine.gsfc.nasa.gov/docs/science/know_l1/cosmic_rays.html\',850,600)">NASA: cosmic ray pages</a> - larger perspective <br/>      <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://helios.gsfc.nasa.gov/cosmic.html\',800,600)">COSMICOPIA: cosmic rays in the news:</a> - current trends   <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://astro.uchicago.edu/cosmus/projects/aires/protonshoweroverchicago.mpeg\',800,600)">COSMUS: cosmic ray simulation:</a> - centered on Chicago (need QuickTime plugin)' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='cosmic_rays';
update comment set body='    <I>    Submit an online poster to share your abstract, procedure, results, and plots. Use our tool to create, save and publish your posters.</I>      <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=create_poster\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>  <P> <B>References</B> <p>      <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'make-edit_posters_static.html\',1000,600)">New Poster Page</a> - build a new poster showing required sections.<br/>   <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'displayPoster.jsp?type=poster&posterName=adlerperformance.data\',750,600)">Example Poster</a> - simple online poster<br/>      <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://leo.stcloudstate.edu/bizwrite/abstracts.html\',750,600)">Writing Abstracts</a> - good abstract tutorial<br/> ' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='create_poster';
update comment set body='<I>Measuring cosmic rays is an indirect process: you cannot see or feel them. It is difficult to be sure that you are measuring what you intend. Other processes can mimic the signal and mix in with the data. You must separate real data from background noise.  <P>  </I> <P><U>Measurement Errors</U> - COMING SOON: detailed discussion of cosmic ray background noise and measurement errors   <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=data_error\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>    <P> <B>References</B>     <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://instruct1.cit.cornell.edu/courses/virtual_lab/LabZero/Experimental_Error.shtml\',800,600)">Experimental Error</a> - general discussion of measurement errors   <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://www.batesville.k12.in.us/physics/APPhyNet/Measurement/Measurement_Intro.html\',800,600)">Physics and Measurements</a> - more specific discussion of errors<br/>' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='data_errors';
update comment set body='     <I>     Scientists must convince each other that their conclusions make sense. Data, analysis and interpretation are tools that show the research details and defend results.</I>       <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=defend_solution\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>  <P> <B>References</B>         <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://www.madsci.org/posts/archives/2004-02/1075755143.Me.r.html\',800,600)">Defend Your Research</a> - focus on the results, not hypothesis<br/> ' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='defend_solution';
update comment set body='The QuarkNet cosmic ray detectors use scintillation material to count cosmic rays.  Other techniques also sense the presence of cosmic rays.  <P> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=defend_solution\',700,600)"> <b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>  <P> <B>References</B>          <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://hires.physics.utah.edu/reading/detect.html\',800,600)"> Detection of UHE Cosmic Rays</a> - tools for sensing cosmic rays<br/>  <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://hires.physics.utah.edu/reading/uhecr.html\',800,600)"> Ultra-High Energy Cosmic Rays</a> - background on UHE cosmic rays<br/>  <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://hires.physics.utah.edu/reading/fluor.html\',800,600)"> History of the Air Fluorescence Technique</a> - Air Fluorescence<br/>  <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://hires.physics.utah.edu/reading/flyseye.html\',800,600)"> The Fly\'s Eye</a> - large cosmic ray project<br/>     ' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='detection_techniques';
update comment set body='<I>All research projects gather data using real hardware that take measurments. Scientists push the limit of their instruments with their questions. Sometimes research questions must wait for new technologies. <P> You need to know what your detector can do.</I> <P>  <P>Let\'s meet the cosmic ray collaboration detectors and see how they work.  <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'ref-detect.jsp\',500,580)">The Detector</A> - measurements detectors make. <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=detector\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A> <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'flash/daq_only_standalone.html\',500,550)">Detector Animation</A> - roll overs show functions of different parts. <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'flash/DAQII.html\',520,550)">Electronic Simulation</A> - shower study data aquisition ' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='detector';
update comment set body=' <I>All successful science projects benefit from a well-designed plan.  The plan provides the roadmap, and it assures no vital component gets left out.</I>     <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'ref-plan.jsp\',600,600)">Plan Outline</A> - Elements that can be included in a research proposal  <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=research_plan\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='research_plan';
update comment set body='    <I>Research centers on a single, well-designed research question.  Knowing the question organizes all aspects of the project.  It determines the model used to predict results. It helps design the research plan which marshals resources of time and money and equipment and manpower.</I>   <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'ref-proposal.jsp\')">Determine Your Study</A> - Things to consider. <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=research_proposal\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='research_proposal';
update comment set body='     <I> Research questions rarely spring fully developed at the beginning of a project. The search requires a mixture of brainstorming and prior, background knowledge about the topic.  The process always benefits from a team approach and iteration.</I>   <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'ref-question.jsp\')">How to begin</A> - develop a research question    <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=research_question\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>  <P> <B>References</B>   <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://pblmm.k12.ca.us/PBLGuide/Activities/BeginningResearch.html\',800,600)">Beginning Research</a> - helpful steps to start<br/>' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='research_question';
update comment set body='     <I>To pursue your research question, you must find data that "fits" your study by searching the cosmic ray database for relevant data.     <P> Setting parameter values allows you to select data files for analysis. These parameters can include:   <UL>   <LI>Date - looking for coincident times. <LI>Location - looking for near-by detectors: state? city? school? <LI>Channels - that is, 1, 2, 3, 4. <LI>Detector configuration - stacked? unstacked? </UL> </I>   <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=search_parameters\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>  <P><B>References</B> <P> <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'tryit_lifetime.html#search_data\',540,380)">Date</a> - example to search the existing data for files by date only <P> <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'tryit_flux.html#search_data\',540,380)">Date <i>and</i> location</a> - example to search the existing data files by date and location' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='search_parameters';
update comment set body='<I>After measuring fundamental quantities, new derived quantities assembled from the fundamentals allow calculation of parameters, which cannot be measured.</I><P> <P> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'ref-calc-derived.jsp\',500,200)">Simple Calculations</A> - Get background and examples.</FONT><BR><P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=simple_calculations\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='simple_calculations';
update comment set body='<FONT SIZE=-1><I>Scientists and engineers communicate with two tools:     <UL>     <LI>text     <LI>graphs and charts     </UL>     Graphs and charts communicate information visually.</I>    <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'ref-graph.jsp\',600,720)">Simple Graph</A> - Get background.    <P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=simple_graphs\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A> <P>   <B>References</B>   <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://nces.ed.gov/nceskids/graphing/\',700,600)">Create a Graph</A> - Intreactive site where you can practice making area, bar and line graphs and pie charts.    <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://www.shodor.org/interactivate/activities/flydata/index.html\',900,600)">Interactive X-Y plot</A> - enter and practice plotting your data.   <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://www.teacherschoice.com.au/images/scientific_plot.gif\',600,650)">Scientific Plot</A> - Example shows line graph with error bars on points and best fit line.     <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A  HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://musr.physics.ubc.ca/~jess/hr/skept/Meas/node2.html\',700,600)">Graphs and Error Bars</A> - A definition.    <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://www.purplemath.com/modules/graphexp.htm\',800,600)">Graphing Exponential Equations</A> - Lessons from Purplemath.   <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://www.shodor.org/interactivate/activities/histogram/\',900,600)">Histogram</A> - The what, how and why of histograms with an interactive example.   <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://www.teacherschoice.com.au/images/histogram.gif\',600,600)">Histogram</A> - Example.   <P STYLE="margin-left: 10px"> <A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'http://www.deakin.edu.au/~agoodman/sci101/chap12.php#RTFToC12\',900,600)">3D Graphs</A> - Examples. ' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='simple_graphs';
update comment set body='  <I>Science builds on measuring something; that\'s how data are generated. You need to know about measurements to study cosmic ray characteristics.</I><P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'ref-simpm.jsp\',600,600)">Simple Measurements</A> - Get background.<P><A HREF="javascript:showRefLink(\'logEntry.jsp?keyword=simple_measurements\',700,600)"><b>Log it!</b><IMG SRC="graphics/logbook_pencil.gif" border="0"  align="middle"></A>' where discriminator='Milestone' and  name='simple_measurement';
